To authenticate itself nokia7650 establishes as ssl connection with a 
web-server, then performs the following request:
GET /login/uploaderLogin.asp?Username=username&Password=password 
HTTP/1.1\r\nHost: https://host.domain.tld\r\n\r\n

Apache replies with a - 400 invalid header -, of course!

OK, you laugh, but I cry!

Follows a *personal* patch to solve this problem:
--- apache_1.3.26/src/main/http_vhost.c Wed Mar 13 22:05:31 2002
+++ apache_1.3.26/src/main/http_vhost_new.c     Thu Sep  5 12:13:56 2002
@@ -719,7 +719,14 @@
                continue;
        }
        if (*src == '/' || *src == '\\') {
+#define NOKIA_7650_BUG 1
+#ifdef NOKIA_7650_BUG
+           src++;
+           dst=host;
+           continue;
+#else
            goto bad;
+#endif
        }
         if (*src == ':') {
             /* check the port part */



